\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Correlations between the error term $\varepsilon $, the endogenous regressor $\bar  {y}$, the instruments $Gx$ and $G^2 x$ across 100 simulations. The plot shows that $\operatorname  {Corr}(\varepsilon , G^2 x)$ is generally smaller than $\operatorname  {Corr}(\varepsilon , Gx)$, confirming that the second-order instrument is less endogenous. }}{6}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:correlations}{{3}{6}{Correlations between the error term $\varepsilon $, the endogenous regressor $\bar {y}$, the instruments $Gx$ and $G^2 x$ across 100 simulations. The plot shows that $\operatorname {Corr}(\varepsilon , G^2 x)$ is generally smaller than $\operatorname {Corr}(\varepsilon , Gx)$, confirming that the second-order instrument is less endogenous}{figure.3}{}}
